SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1233
By Lamar
A RESOLUTION to commend Bennie Smith of Shelby County for
his honorable and astute service on the
Tennessee State Election Commission.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those citizens who have performed with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm as
public servants; and
WHEREAS, Bennie Smith of Shelby County is one such individual, who has been an
invaluable asset as a member of the State Election Commission and recently completed his
appointed term of office; and
WHEREAS, an analytics and technology professional with deep experience across
public service, finance, and enterprise innovation, Bennie Smith was appointed to the Shelby
County Election Commission in 2019 and to the Tennessee State Election Commission in 2022
to represent the citizens of West Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, a software developer and financial analytics leader, Mr. Smith is currently
the Motor Vehicle Registration Administrator for the Shelby County Clerk's Office, having
previously enjoyed tenures as an employee with ABB, Thomas & Betts, and Hilton Worldwide
and in municipal government; and
WHEREAS, nationally recognized for applying data integrity, audit rigor, and financial
controls to elections systems and public governance, Mr. Smith has been featured in Bloomberg
Businessweek, PBS, and USA Today; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Smith is an individual whose benevolence, acumen, and strong
commitment to public service have helped to enhance the well-being of this State and its
citizens; and
SJR1233
018251
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Bennie Smith has demonstrated the utmost professionalism, ability, and
integrity, winning the unbridled respect and admiration of his colleagues and a grateful State;
now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby commend Bennie Smith for his
honorable and astute service to the good people of Tennessee as a member of the Tennessee
State Election Commission, commend his ongoing commitment to public service, and thank him
for a difficult job well done.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
